name: Turning Japanese
description: A practice of understanding cultural harmony through the brands we mutually consume. Many of the Japanese brands I considered quintessentially American as a child, perfectly woven into the fabric of my Americano upbringing. I was unable to discern them as having an alternate origin. Symbols transform as their meaning unfolds from one habitation to another. Turning Japanese seems to have a wide range contexts when the foreign population of Japan seems to be less than 3%, though internationally I feel we all proudly embrace them as a part of us.
